name: Set
title: Set - God of Chaos & Desert | Egyptian Mythology
subtitle: God of Chaos, Desert, Storms, and Foreigners
shortDescription: Set is the god of chaos, the desert, storms, and disorder. Red-haired and fierce, Set murdered his brother Osiris but was defeated by Horus . Though often cast as villain, Set also defended Ra's solar barque against the chaos serpent Apep nightly. He represents necessary disorder, the wild desert, and the power of storms.
